Alter Table :-
The alter table statement is used to add , delete or modify columns in an existing table.
1) Add : It is used to add new column to the table.
SYNTAX:    ALTER TABLE < table name > 
           ADD < column name > < data type > ;

#Add new column emp_experience-
ALTER TABLE employee
ADD emp_experience int;

2) DROP : Used to drop existing column from the table.
Syntax:     ALTER TABLE < table name > 
            DROP COLUMN < column name > ;

# Delete "emp_experience" column from the table "employee"-
ALTER TABLE employee
ADD column emp_experience ;

3) MODIFY : Used to modify data type of column.
SYNTAX:      ALTER TABLE < table name > 
             MODIFY < column name > < data type > ;

# Modify datatype of emp_names as varchar(50)-
ALTER TABLE employee
MODIFY emp_name varchar(50) ;

4) RENAME : Used to rename the existing column name.
SYNTAX:      ALTER TABLE < table name > 
            RENAME COLUMN < old_column_name > to <new_column_name> ;

# Rename column "emp_name" as "employee_name"-
ALTER TABLE employee
RENAME COLUMN emp_name
to employee_name ;
RENAME

